We have to pose it as a design question, then.  Is it intended that melee stuns are unaffected by Determination, and if so, then the language describing the RA should be changed (I always first assumed it worked against shield stuns until a few losses to a paladin. *cry*)  If ithat's not the case, then a few logs should be able to prove that it's not in fact working against melee stuns (log a fight vs. a minstrel and a s/s paladin).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Regarding Dirt</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I do think Dirt might want to be mentioned in the next TL report, but we should have logs of its actual effectiveness to back it up.  This is often hard since having others' combat turned on makes it almost impossible to read combat spam (not that it's not hard enough), but I really have a sinking feeling that in open field RvR it's just not working nearly as effectively as TW or Zerk.  It can be powerful when it does work, especially against melees with long delay weapons, but I'd be interested to see the actual effect of it.<br>
<br>
This might be a good thing to ask for in the next report, for all melees... any change of making parry/evade/block another item that can be assigned a color or just given another color, maybe green or something?  It would help a lot I think, but it's relatively minor.<br>
<br>
