sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). It's more of a general RA though - can be used in every situation. Determination, while real good, only helps reduce CC. Now that PBAoE is the new rage, CC reduction won't help a whole lot. It's really based on what you feel you encounter, or will encounter, the most. Free health bar, or lesser waiting time? Can also get higher Det or IP at some other point in your career.<br>
<br>
First Aid, I thought was stupid. But i'm actually using it from time to time. I'm often not targetted in RvR (probably due to my reputation, but i'm sure the merc classes design make me an unpopular target), so I'm often able to fire it off in the middle of battle. Heck, standing still for 7 seconds, people probably think i'm CCed..<br>
<br>
Bezerkers (of all people <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) get Avoid Pain. Blademasters and Mercenarys do not. Giving us access to this Realm Ability will give us more of what we really lack (survivability). I don't really know if blademasters should get this ability (though it's open for discussion), as their current armor + evade proves more defense than ours. However, even though it does prove higher effectivness, they may still need a boost to AF in order to &quot;stay in the game&quot;. This is a question more awnserable by someone who's played a blademaster in the end game (in other words, not me).<br>
<br>
I DO NOT like the idea of having to get an RA to make us equal to everyone else (befor their RAs are accounted for). None the less, this RA will do what it was originally intended (a bonus to AF when used) for us once the mercenary class has been &quot;fixed&quot;. Currently, it will be used more in the fashion of &quot;I must use this in order to stand a chance&quot;, instead of a better chance (IMO).<br>
<br>
This is at least one solid reason, but we'll need more than one. While the fact that our survivability needs improving, that could be solved by designs on the merc, not his RAs. The fact that Bezerkers get it IS a reason, though it will appear flimsy and &quot;weak&quot;. Another approach could be because of our RolePlaying Cause.. <br>
<br>
A Mercenary is someone who devotes himself to killing his current target(s). However, it's common knowledge to us and him that there will be times better spent being defensive (wearing out an opponent, for example). The Mercenary, while favoring offense, isn't a fool and will take advantage of whatever he can (this man throws dirt at people for gods sake). Avoid Pain represents him being more cautious than he usually is. It shows that he would rather turn his body over a bit so a sword lands on a more protected spot instead of a weaker spot. He trys to 'roll with the blows' and falls back after a jab to his chest, only to roll backwards and stand up. Because this takes more effert than normal, Avoid Pain works perfectly in representing these moves while also representing that he's only able to do these for so long and so often (re-use timer and how long the effects last). A Mercenary is someone who uses everything he can, including his brain. Not an idiot who blindly swings his weapons in the general direction of his target(s).<br>
<br>
This is all I can think of at the moment. Hope it gives people some inspiration. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
